    style C fill:#3b82f6,stroke:#2563eb,color:#fff
    style D fill:#ef4444,stroke:#dc2626,color:#fff
```

### 2.4 Operating Environment

**Client-side:**
- Modern web browsers (Chrome 90+, Firefox 88+, Safari 14+, Edge 90+)
- JavaScript enabled
- Microphone access for voice interviews
- Minimum screen resolution: 375x667 (mobile), 1024x768 (desktop)

**Server-side:**
- Node.js 18+ runtime
- Vercel serverless deployment
- Firebase Cloud Firestore
- Firebase Authentication
- Firebase Storage / Cloudinary

### 2.5 Design and Implementation Constraints

- Must comply with GDPR and data privacy regulations
- Must use Firebase for backend services
- Real-time voice processing requires stable internet connection (min 1 Mbps)
- Browser must support WebRTC for voice functionality
- Must implement role-based access control
- Must support responsive design for mobile and desktop

### 2.6 Assumptions and Dependencies

**Assumptions:**
- Users have reliable internet connectivity
- Users have functional microphones for voice interviews
- Firebase services remain available and operational
- AI API services (Gemini, Vapi) maintain uptime

**Dependencies:**
- Firebase Authentication and Firestore
- Google Gemini API availability
- Vapi AI service availability
- Cloudinary service for media storage
- Third-party npm packages and libraries

