## 3. System Features

### 3.1 User Management

#### 3.1.1 User Registration

**Priority:** High  
**Description:** Allow new users to register with email/password

**Functional Requirements:**
- **FR-1.1:** System shall accept email and password for registration
- **FR-1.2:** System shall validate email format and password strength
- **FR-1.3:** System shall allow users to select role (Candidate or HR)
- **FR-1.4:** System shall send verification email
- **FR-1.5:** HR registrations shall require admin approval
- **FR-1.6:** System shall create user profile in Firestore upon successful registration

**Use Case Diagram:**

```mermaid
graph LR
    U[User] -->|Register| S1[Registration Form]
    S1 -->|Submit| S2{Validate Input}
    S2 -->|Valid| S3[Create Account]
    S2 -->|Invalid| S4[Show Error]
    S3 -->|Candidate| S5[Activate Account]
    S3 -->|HR| S6[Pending Approval]
    S5 --> S7[Redirect to Dashboard]
    S6 --> S8[Notify Admin]
    
    style S3 fill:#10b981,stroke:#059669,color:#fff
    style S4 fill:#ef4444,stroke:#dc2626,color:#fff
```

#### 3.1.2 User Authentication

**Priority:** High  
**Description:** Secure login/logout functionality

**Functional Requirements:**
- **FR-1.7:** System shall authenticate users via Firebase Authentication
- **FR-1.8:** System shall support email/password login
- **FR-1.9:** System shall provide "Forgot Password" functionality
- **FR-1.10:** System shall maintain session state
- **FR-1.11:** System shall redirect users based on role after login
- **FR-1.12:** System shall provide logout functionality

#### 3.1.3 Profile Management

**Priority:** Medium  
**Description:** Users can view and update their profiles

**Functional Requirements:**
- **FR-1.13:** Users shall be able to update display name and photo
- **FR-1.14:** Candidates shall be able to add skills, experience level, and years of experience
- **FR-1.15:** Candidates shall be able to upload/update resume (PDF)
- **FR-1.16:** HR users shall be able to add company information
- **FR-1.17:** System shall validate file uploads (type, size)

### 3.2 Interview Management (Candidate)

#### 3.2.1 Create Interview Session

**Priority:** High  
**Description:** Candidates can create customized mock interview sessions

**Functional Requirements:**
- **FR-2.1:** System shall allow candidates to specify job role
- **FR-2.2:** System shall allow selection of technology stack (multiple)
- **FR-2.3:** System shall allow selection of experience level
- **FR-2.4:** System shall allow duration selection (15, 30, 45, 60 minutes)
- **FR-2.5:** System shall generate role-specific questions using Gemini AI
- **FR-2.6:** System shall create interview document in Firestore

**Sequence Diagram - Interview Creation:**

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant C as Candidate
    participant UI as Frontend
    participant API as API Route
    participant Gemini as Gemini AI
    participant DB as Firestore
    
    C->>UI: Fill interview form
    UI->>API: POST /api/interviews/create
    API->>API: Validate input
    API->>Gemini: Generate questions
    Gemini-->>API: Return questions
    API->>DB: Create interview doc
    DB-->>API: Interview ID
    API-->>UI: Success + Interview ID
    UI-->>C: Redirect to interview
```

#### 3.2.2 Conduct Voice Interview

**Priority:** High  
**Description:** Real-time voice-based interview with AI

**Functional Requirements:**
- **FR-2.7:** System shall initialize Vapi AI client with assistant ID
- **FR-2.8:** System shall request microphone permission
- **FR-2.9:** System shall start voice conversation when user clicks "Start Interview"
- **FR-2.10:** System shall display questions one by one
- **FR-2.11:** System shall capture audio responses and convert to text
- **FR-2.12:** System shall provide visual feedback during recording
- **FR-2.13:** System shall allow users to end interview early
- **FR-2.14:** System shall save transcript to Firestore
- **FR-2.15:** System shall update interview status to "completed"

#### 3.2.3 View Feedback

**Priority:** High  
**Description:** Display detailed AI-generated feedback

**Functional Requirements:**
- **FR-2.16:** System shall generate feedback upon interview completion
- **FR-2.17:** System shall display overall score (0-100)
- **FR-2.18:** System shall display category scores (communication, technical, problem-solving, confidence)
- **FR-2.19:** System shall display strengths and weaknesses
- **FR-2.20:** System shall provide improvement tips
- **FR-2.21:** System shall allow PDF download of feedback
- **FR-2.22:** System shall display transcript with question-answer pairs

### 3.3 Job and Candidate Management (HR)

#### 3.3.1 Job Posting Management

**Priority:** High  
**Description:** HR can create and manage job openings

**Functional Requirements:**
- **FR-3.1:** HR shall be able to create new job posting
- **FR-3.2:** System shall require job title, description, requirements, tech stack
- **FR-3.3:** HR shall be able to set experience level, location, salary range
- **FR-3.4:** HR shall be able to publish, draft, or close job postings
- **FR-3.5:** HR shall be able to edit existing job postings
- **FR-3.6:** HR shall be able to delete job postings
- **FR-3.7:** System shall display list of all jobs for the HR's company

#### 3.3.2 Candidate Invitation

**Priority:** Medium  
**Description:** HR can invite candidates to interview for specific job

**Functional Requirements:**
- **FR-3.8:** HR shall be able to send interview invitation via email
- **FR-3.9:** System shall allow HR to include custom message
- **FR-3.10:** System shall set expiration date for invitation
- **FR-3.11:** System shall track invitation status (pending, accepted, declined, expired)
- **FR-3.12:** System shall notify HR when invitation is accepted

#### 3.3.3 Candidate Review

**Priority:** High  
**Description:** HR can review candidate interview results

**Functional Requirements:**
- **FR-3.13:** HR shall view list of all candidates who interviewed
- **FR-3.14:** HR shall view candidate profile and resume
- **FR-3.15:** HR shall view interview feedback and scores
- **FR-3.16:** HR shall view interview transcript
- **FR-3.17:** HR shall view interview recording (if available)
- **FR-3.18:** HR shall be able to rate candidates (1-5 stars)
- **FR-3.19:** HR shall be able to add notes
- **FR-3.20:** HR shall be able to shortlist candidates

### 3.4 Administrative Functions

#### 3.4.1 User Management

**Priority:** High  
**Description:** Admin can manage all platform users

**Functional Requirements:**
- **FR-4.1:** Admin shall view all users with filters (role, status)
- **FR-4.2:** Admin shall approve pending HR accounts
- **FR-4.3:** Admin shall suspend or activate user accounts
- **FR-4.4:** Admin shall delete user accounts
- **FR-4.5:** Admin shall view user details and activity

#### 3.4.2 Platform Analytics

**Priority:** Medium  
**Description:** Admin can view system-wide metrics

**Functional Requirements:**
- **FR-4.6:** Admin shall view total users count (by role)
- **FR-4.7:** Admin shall view total interviews conducted
- **FR-4.8:** Admin shall view total companies registered
- **FR-4.9:** Admin shall view total jobs posted
- **FR-4.10:** Admin shall view growth trends over time
- **FR-4.11:** Admin shall view active vs. inactive users

#### 3.4.3 System Settings

**Priority:** Medium  
**Description:** Admin can configure platform settings

**Functional Requirements:**
- **FR-4.12:** Admin shall enable/disable maintenance mode
- **FR-4.13:** Admin shall enable/disable new registrations
- **FR-4.14:** Admin shall enable/disable HR registrations
- **FR-4.15:** Admin shall configure max interview duration
- **FR-4.16:** Admin shall enable/disable AI features
- **FR-4.17:** System shall validate and save settings to Firestore

---

## 4. External Interface Requirements

### 4.1 User Interfaces

#### 4.1.1 General UI Requirements

- **UI-1:** All pages shall be responsive (mobile, tablet, desktop)
- **UI-2:** System shall support dark and light themes
- **UI-3:** System shall provide smooth transitions and animations
- **UI-4:** System shall use consistent design system (Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui)
- **UI-5:** System shall provide visual feedback for all user actions
- **UI-6:** System shall display loading states during async operations
- **UI-7:** System shall show error messages in user-friendly format

#### 4.1.2 Landing Page

- **UI-8:** Display value proposition and key features
- **UI-9:** Provide "Get Started" and "Sign In" CTAs
- **UI-10:** Include feature showcase with glassmorphism cards
- **UI-11:** Display "How It Works" section with step-by-step guide
- **UI-12:** Include social proof (testimonials, user count)

#### 4.1.3 Dashboard Layouts

**Candidate Dashboard:**
- Statistics cards (total interviews, average score, improvement)
- Recent interviews list
- Quick action buttons (New Interview, View History)

**HR Dashboard:**
- Statistics cards (active jobs, total candidates, shortlisted)
- Recent candidates list
- Active job postings
- Quick action buttons (Create Job, Invite Candidate)

**Admin Dashboard:**
- Platform statistics (users, interviews, jobs)
- Recent user registrations
- Pending HR approvals
- System health indicators

### 4.2 Hardware Interfaces

- **HW-1:** Microphone for voice input during interviews
- **HW-2:** Speakers/headphones for AI voice output
- **HW-3:** Camera (optional, for future video analysis)

### 4.3 Software Interfaces

#### 4.3.1 Firebase Services

| Service | Purpose | Data Exchange |
|---------|---------|---------------|
| **Firebase Authentication** | User authentication | User credentials, session tokens |
| **Cloud Firestore** | NoSQL database | JSON documents for all collections |
| **Firebase Storage** | File storage | Resume PDFs, profile photos |

#### 4.3.2 AI Services

| Service | Purpose | API Endpoint |
|---------|---------|--------------|
| **Google Gemini AI** | Question generation, feedback analysis | REST API with API key authentication |
| **Vapi AI** | Real-time voice interviews | WebSocket + REST API |

#### 4.3.3 Media Storage

| Service | Purpose | Integration |
|---------|---------|-------------|
| **Cloudinary** | Video recording storage | REST API for upload/retrieval |

### 4.4 Communication Interfaces

- **HTTP/HTTPS:** All client-server communication via HTTPS
- **WebSocket:** Real-time voice communication via Vapi
- **REST API:** Standard JSON-based API endpoints
- **Email:** SMTP for sending notifications (via Firebase or third-party service)

