## 7. Non-Functional Requirements

### 7.1 Performance Requirements

**NFR-1: Response Time**
- Page load time: < 2 seconds for initial load
- API response time: < 500ms for standard queries
- AI question generation: < 5 seconds
- Feedback generation: < 10 seconds

**NFR-2: Throughput**
- Support 1000+ concurrent users
- Handle 100+ simultaneous interviews
- Process 10,000+ database operations per minute

**NFR-3: Resource Usage**
- Client-side bundle size: < 500KB (gzipped)
- Database read/write optimization
- Efficient caching strategies

### 7.2 Security Requirements

**NFR-4: Authentication & Authorization**
- All routes protected with Firebase Authentication
- Role-based access control (RBAC) enforced server-side
- Session tokens expire after 24 hours
- Password requirements: min 8 chars, alphanumeric

**NFR-5: Data Protection**
- All data transmitted via HTTPS/TLS 1.3
- API keys stored in environment variables
- Firestore security rules enforced
- User data encrypted at rest

**NFR-6: Privacy**
- GDPR compliance for user data
- User consent for data collection
- Right to data deletion
- Secure handling of personal information

### 7.3 Reliability Requirements

**NFR-7: Availability**
- System uptime: 99.5% monthly
- Automatic failover for critical services
- Graceful degradation when AI services unavailable

**NFR-8: Error Handling**
- Comprehensive error logging
- User-friendly error messages
- Automatic retry for transient failures
- Rollback capabilities for failed transactions

**NFR-9: Backup & Recovery**
- Daily automated Firestore backups
- Point-in-time recovery capability
- Disaster recovery plan documented

### 7.4 Maintainability Requirements

**NFR-10: Code Quality**
- TypeScript for type safety
- ESLint for code linting
- Consistent code formatting
- Component-based architecture

**NFR-11: Documentation**
- API documentation for all endpoints
- Code comments for complex logic
- README for setup instructions
- Architecture diagrams maintained

**NFR-12: Testability**
- Unit tests for critical functions
- Integration tests for API routes
- Manual testing procedures documented

### 7.5 Usability Requirements

**NFR-13: User Experience**
- Intuitive navigation structure
- Consistent UI/UX across all pages
- Mobile-responsive design (375px+)
- Accessibility: WCAG 2.1 Level AA compliance

**NFR-14: Feedback & Guidance**
- Clear error messages with resolution steps
- Loading states for async operations
- Success confirmations for actions
- Helpful tooltips and help text

**NFR-15: Internationalization**
- UTF-8 character encoding
- Date/time formatting based on locale
- Future support for multi-language (planned)

### 7.6 Scalability Requirements

**NFR-16: Horizontal Scaling**
- Serverless architecture on Vercel
- Auto-scaling based on demand
- Stateless API design

**NFR-17: Database Scaling**
- Firestore automatic sharding
- Indexed queries for performance
- Denormalization where appropriate

### 7.7 Compatibility Requirements

**NFR-18: Browser Compatibility**
- Chrome 90+
- Firefox 88+
- Safari 14+
- Edge 90+
- Mobile browsers (iOS Safari, Chrome Mobile)

**NFR-19: Device Compatibility**
- Desktop (Windows, macOS, Linux)
- Tablets (iPad, Android tablets)
- Mobile phones (iOS, Android)

### 7.8 Compliance Requirements

**NFR-20: Legal & Regulatory**
- GDPR compliance (EU)
- CCPA compliance (California)
- Data retention policies
- Terms of Service and Privacy Policy

